  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nHit the following error from `truffle test` from automation:\r\n```\r\nError: CompileError: truffle/DeployedAddresses.sol:4:75: ParserError: Expected ';' but got 'ILLEGAL'\r\nfunction Migrations() public pure returns (address payable) { return 0.5.80d0c2BF6239b1E58211E0B6510e1Fa1650717; }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe problem is that this regex can match `0<anything>5<anything>0` in the ethereum addresss, and replace that with the current compiler version such as `0.5.8`:\r\nhttps://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/9acc723e6942fa059290fc7cbcfc3e83110bd444/packages/truffle-core/lib/testing/deployed.js#L42\r\n\r\nMy suggestion for a fix is to change the regex to `source.replace(/0\\.5\\.0/gm, v);` - I will try and submit a PR along side this issue.\r\n\r\nHere's some quick node output to show what I mean:\r\n```\r\n> let a = '0a5b0c'; // this clearly isn't a solc version\r\nundefined\r\n> a.replace(/0.5.0/gm, '0.5.8'); // but this still replaces the `a` and `b`\r\n'0.5.8c'\r\n> a.replace(/0\\.5\\.0/gm, '0.5.8'); // where as this works fine\r\n'0a5b0c'\r\n> let b = '0.5.0'\r\nundefined\r\n> b.replace(/0\\.5\\.0/gm, '0.5.8'); // and still replaces an actual solc version\r\n'0.5.8'\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nIt is a random occurrence, so you would need to run truffle test a lot of times to hit this.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`trufle test` runs\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: CompileError: truffle/DeployedAddresses.sol:4:75: ParserError: Expected ';' but got 'ILLEGAL'\r\nfunction Migrations() public pure returns (address payable) { return 0.5.80d0c2BF6239b1E58211E0B6510e1Fa1650717; }\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Linux\r\n* Ethereum client: Geth/PoA (in Kaleido)\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 0.5.27\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v10.15.3\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.7.0\r\n",
